    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style of Chinese script that is the most unrestricted among cursive scripts, first seen in the 8th century CE. It is so named because it features writing in fast speed, linking strokes and characters together. In addition, the characters are sometimes greatly varied in size and shape. It is particularly valued for its untrammeled and uninhibited quality.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
